# The filesystem hierarchy

**No drive letters.** Every disk, device, and file hangs off one tree rooted at **`/`**.

## The ones that matter

- **`/home`** ‚Äî your stuff (`/home/<you>`)
- **`/etc`** ‚Äî **config**, plain-text, editable
- **`/var`** ‚Äî changes at runtime ‚Äî **`/var/log`**
- **`/tmp`** ‚Äî scratch, wiped on reboot
- **`/usr`** ‚Äî installed software (`/usr/bin`)
- **`/boot`** ‚Äî kernel + bootloader
- **`/dev`** ‚Äî device files (`/dev/sda`, `/dev/null`)
- **`/proc`, `/sys`** ‚Äî **virtual**, not on disk

## Don't memorise ‚Äî remember four

1. config ‚Üí **`/etc`**
2. your stuff ‚Üí **`/home/<you>`**
3. logs ‚Üí **`/var/log`**
4. scratch ‚Üí **`/tmp`**

The rest you'll meet as you need them.
